					{
						"analysis": "Package: Jinja2 (whl)\nVersion: 3.1.6\nDescription: A very fast and expressive template engine.\n\nThe package is a supply chain attack masquerading as the legitimate 'Jinja2' library (version 3.1.6). The source code does not contain the expected templating engine logic as its primary component; instead, it is structured as an NVDA (NonVisual Desktop Access) screen reader plugin named 'AI-assistant'. Most critically, the package includes logic in 'globalPlugins/AI-assistant/ui/host_process.py' to execute a bundled Windows binary ('nvda_ui_host.exe') using subprocess.Popen. It also contains functionality to download and execute additional payloads (AI models) via the 'ollama' CLI. The use of a highly trusted package name to distribute unrelated code that executes bundled binaries and manages external AI service connections is a clear indicator of a supply chain compromise or masquerading attack.",
